        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 3. — Isolated dental remains of Hyotherium lacaillei n. sp. from Béon 1 (Montréal-du-Gers, Gers, France, MN4): 1, left p1, MHNT Béon G4 537 (a, buccal; b, posterior; c, lingual; d, anterior); 2, left i1, MHNT Béon 92 G3 1170 (a, lingual; b, mesial); 3, right i2, MHNT Béon 93 G4 468 (a, lingual; b, mesial); 4, left m2-m3, MHNT Béon AR SN 6, MHNT Béon AR SN 4 (a, occlusal; b, lingual); 5, left I1, MHNT Béon 92 G3 111 (a, lingual; b, distal); 6, left I2, MHNT Béon AR SN 2 (a, mesial; b, lingual; c, distal; d, labial); 7, right I3, MHNT Béon AR SN 3 (a, mesial; b, lingual; c, distal; d, labial); 8, right Cm, MHNT Béon AR SN 1 (a, lingual; b, anterior). Scale bars: 1-5, 8, 2 cm; 6, 7, 1 cm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4651016/files/figure.png" .

